ðŸ”¹ Problem 1: Mean, Variance & Standard Deviation


import numpy as np
from scipy import stats

# Generate random data
data = np.random.randn(10)

# Statistical measures
mean = stats.tmean(data)
variance = stats.tvar(data)
std_dev = stats.tstd(data)

print("Mean:", mean)
print("Variance:", variance)
print("Standard Deviation:", std_dev)



ðŸ”¹ Problem 2: Least Squares Method (Best-Fit Line)


import numpy as np
from scipy.linalg import lstsq

# Generate data
x = np.arange(10)
y = 2*x + 1 + np.random.randn(10)

# Least squares calculation
A = np.vstack([x, np.ones(len(x))]).T
m, c = lstsq(A, y)[0]


ðŸ§  MEMORY FLOW (VERY IMPORTANT)

Generate Data â†’ SciPy Function â†’ Print Result

If you remember this flow, you can rebuild the code anytime.

print("Equation of line: y =", m, "x +", c)

